-----------------------------------------------------
-= Installing Voise res_speech module on Asterisk =-
-----------------------------------------------------

Voise connector for Asterisk Generic Speech Recognition API.
(http://www.asterisk.org/doxygen/1.4/AstSpeech.html)

In order to install 'res_speech_voise' module, you need to perform the following steps:

1 - Copy 'res_speech_voise.c' file to 'res' folder (ex: /usr/src/asterisk-12.8.2/res) of your asterisk sources.
    and copy 'app_verbio_speech.c' file to 'apps' folder of your asterisk sources.

2 - Edit the 'Makefile' ('res' folder) in order to add (before 'all:' label):

    2a - for Asterisk 1.4, 1.6 o 1.8: 

    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise
    
    2b - for Asterisk 11:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=110000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    2c - for Asterisk 12:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=120000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    2d - for Asterisk 13:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=130000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_res_speech_voise+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

3 - Edit the 'Makefile' ('apps' folder) in order to add:

    3a - If you are on Asterisk 1.2

    APPS+=app_voise_speech.so
    
    and
    
    app_voise_speech.so : app_voise_speech.o
        $(CC) $(SOLINK) -o $@ ${CYGSOLINK} $< ${CYGSOLIB} -lvoise

    --------------

    3b - If you are on Asterisk 1.4, 1.6 or 1.8, add before 'all:' label:
    
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_app_voise_speech+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    --------------

    3c - If you are on Asterisk 11, add before 'all:' label:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=110000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_app_voise_speech+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    ---------------

    3d - If you are on Asterisk 12, add before 'all:' label:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=120000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_app_voise_speech+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

    ---------------

    3e - If you are on Asterisk 13, add before 'all:' label:

    _ASTCFLAGS+=-DASTERISK_VERSION_NUM=130000
    MENUSELECT_DEPENDS_app_voise_speech+=VOISE
    VOISE_LIB=-lvoise

4 - Run 'make install' (top of your asterisk sources)

5 - Check that you have the following lines in /etc/asterisk/modules.conf:

; Uncomment the following if you wish to use the Speech Recognition API
preload => res_speech.so
load => res_speech_voise.so

6 - Copy 'voise.conf' (configuration file) to:

/etc/asterisk